args: Um, there's no rope? She usually hangs it\nout of her window for me, so...
Ah! S-someone's coming!\nI have to hide!
Huh? Thought I saw someone just now.
I bet it's that cad who's carrying letters to\ntrick the young miss into marriage!
(Th-they know about the elopement!\n...And about ME!)
Might still be lurking in the shadows...\nOy! Over here! I need backup!
Ho there! Did you find our man?!
I saw a shadow moving this way, but then\nI lost it. Here, help me beat the bushes.
(Oooh, this is bad... If I stay here,\nI'm as good as caught.)
(But if they know about the elopement,\nthere's no point in delivering this letter\nanyway. I have to run.)
My future with Julia rests in your hands!
(...No. It's not up to me to decide if there's\na point to making a delivery or not.)
(Only its recipient can make that call...\nwhich means I must get it to Julia.)
(Okay... Let me see if I can find a rock\naround here... Ah! There we are.)
(Whew! I made it into the manor.)
(Oh, but security is just as tight in here!)
(Okay, Noelle. Be calm... Be careful...\nWatch their movements closely...)
Very good. Next, I must attend to the...
...Goodness! The master is calling!\nAnd to think I nearly missed it, my word.
What do I do, what do I DOOO?!\nIf anyone heard that, I'm...
Whew! Okay, I think I'm safe.
Er, but what is this room? I just jumped\nin here when I saw it was empty, but...
I think it might be a storage closet.\nThere's lots of random... Huh? What's this?
Oh, there's a letter inside! Looks old...
Wh-what?! Am I reading this right?!
B-but if this is... No, it has to be!
If this works, it could solve everything!\nJulia and Remuel could meet out in\nthe open whenever they wanted!
